com.facebook.collections

Interface SetMap<K,V,S extends Set<V>>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - type for the key
    V - type of the elements in the set
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<Map.Entry<K,S>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConcurrentSetMap, SetMapImpl, TrackableSetMap

    public interface SetMap<K,V,S extends Set<V>>
extends Iterable<Map.Entry<K,S>>
    Map> that is thread-safe. Adding an element V to the set for K will create a set if it doesn't exist already. Conversely, if a set for K becomes empty when removing an item V, the entry for K is removed
